This paper is primarily focused on cybersecurity and detecting fraudulent activity through machine learning methods. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes the use of LSTM neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of an interactive visual interface, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of domain-specific knowledge to improve behavior modeling, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
